te highest. This is the <b data-path-to-node=3D"5" data-index-in-node=3D"12=
6">Maximum Power Point</b>.</p><ul data-path-to-node=3D"6"><li><p data-path=
-to-node=3D"6,0,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"6,0,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">=
The Problem:</b> This "sweet spot" moves constantly based on sunlight inten=
sity and panel temperature.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"6,1,0"><b d=
ata-path-to-node=3D"6,1,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">The MPPT Solution:</b> =
The controller constantly "tracks" this point by adjusting the resistance i=
t presents to the panel, ensuring it pulls the most possible wattage at any=
 given second.</p></li></ul><hr data-path-to-node=3D"7"><h2 data-path-to-no=
de=3D"8">2. DC-to-DC Conversion</h2><p data-path-to-node=3D"9">This is the =
"magic" part. Standard controllers (PWM) simply toggle the connection betwe=
en the panel and the battery. If your panel produces <b data-path-to-node=
=3D"9" data-index-in-node=3D"140">18V</b> but your battery is at <b data-pa=
th-to-node=3D"9" data-index-in-node=3D"167">12V</b>, a PWM controller force=
s the panel down to <b data-path-to-node=3D"9" data-index-in-node=3D"214">1=
2V</b>, wasting the extra voltage.</p><p data-path-to-node=3D"10">An MPPT c=
ontroller acts as a sophisticated <b data-path-to-node=3D"10" data-index-in=
-node=3D"43">DC-to-DC converter</b>:</p><ol start=3D"1" data-path-to-node=
=3D"11"><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"11,0,0">It takes the high-voltage, low-=
current DC from the panels.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"11,1,0">It =
converts it into the exact voltage the battery needs to charge.</p></li><li=
><p data-path-to-node=3D"11,2,0">Crucially, it <b data-path-to-node=3D"11,2=
,0" data-index-in-node=3D"14">increases the current (amperage)</b> to compe=
nsate for the drop in voltage.</p></li></ol><blockquote data-path-to-node=
=3D"12"><p data-path-to-node=3D"12,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"12,0" data-in=
dex-in-node=3D"0">The Conservation of Energy:</b> Since <span class=3D"math=
-inline" data-math=3D"P =3D V \times I" data-index-in-node=3D"34"><span cla=
ss=3D"katex"><span class=3D"katex-html" aria-hidden=3D"true"><span class=3D=
"base"><span class=3D"strut" style=3D"height: 0.6833em;"></span><span class=
