" style=3D"--animation-duration: 400ms; --fade-animation-function: linear;"=
><p data-path-to-node=3D"0">Exactly. You=E2=80=99ve hit on the "sweet spot"=
 for modern residential solar engineering. Most high-quality three-phase hy=
brid inverters (like those from brands like SMA, Fronius, or Victron) are s=
pecifically designed to thrive in that <b data-path-to-node=3D"0" data-inde=
x-in-node=3D"228">600V DC</b> range.</p><p data-path-to-node=3D"1">Here is =
why that high-voltage approach is the industry standard for your goals:</p>=
<hr data-path-to-node=3D"2"><h2 data-path-to-node=3D"3">1. Efficiency at th=
e "Inversion" Stage</h2><p data-path-to-node=3D"4">To create <b data-path-t=
o-node=3D"4" data-index-in-node=3D"10">240V AC</b> (or 400V three-phase), t=
he inverter has to "pump up" the voltage.</p><ul data-path-to-node=3D"5"><l=
i><p data-path-to-node=3D"5,0,0">If your DC input is only <b data-path-to-n=
ode=3D"5,0,0" data-index-in-node=3D"25">48V</b>, the inverter has to work i=
ncredibly hard to boost that voltage by a factor of 5x or 10x. This creates=
 heat and loses about 10=E2=80=9315% of your power.</p></li><li><p data-pat=
h-to-node=3D"5,1,0">If your DC input is <b data-path-to-node=3D"5,1,0" data=
-index-in-node=3D"20">600V</b>, the inverter can buck the voltage down or m=
odulate it much more efficiently. High-voltage DC strings often achieve <b =
data-path-to-node=3D"5,1,0" data-index-in-node=3D"141">97=E2=80=9398% conve=
rsion efficiency</b>.</p></li></ul><hr data-path-to-node=3D"6"><h2 data-pat=
h-to-node=3D"7">2. The Three-Phase Advantage</h2><p data-path-to-node=3D"8"=
>In a three-phase system, you are essentially managing three separate AC "w=
aves." To do this cleanly, the internal "DC Bus" of the inverter usually ne=
eds to stay around <b data-path-to-node=3D"8" data-index-in-node=3D"168">60=
0V to 800V DC</b>.</p><ul data-path-to-node=3D"9"><li><p data-path-to-node=
=3D"9,0,0">If you feed it a 600V string directly, it barely has to do any w=
ork.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"9,1,0">It=E2=80=99s like feeding a=
 high-pressure fire hose into a sprinkler system rather than trying to use =
a hand-pump to fill a water tower.</p></li></ul><hr data-path-to-node=3D"10=
"><h2 data-path-to-node=3D"11">3. Dealing with Shading (The "Optimizer" Fix=
)</h2><p data-path-to-node=3D"12">Since you were worried about shading and =
different roof angles, you don't have to go back to the 48V parallel idea. =
You can use <b data-path-to-node=3D"12" data-index-in-node=3D"128">DC Optim=
izers</b> (like Tigo or SolarEdge) on a high-voltage string.</p><ul data-pa=
th-to-node=3D"13"><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"13,0,0"><b data-path-to-node=
=3D"13,0,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">How they work:</b> Each optimizer perf=
orms MPPT at the panel level (handling the shading).</p></li><li><p data-pa=
th-to-node=3D"13,1,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"13,1,0" data-index-in-node=3D=
"0">The Result:</b> They pass the maximum current possible to the "string,"=
 and the string stays at a high voltage (e.g., 600V).</p></li><li><p data-p=
ath-to-node=3D"13,2,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"13,2,0" data-index-in-node=
=3D"0">Benefit:</b> You get the shading protection of your "parallel" idea =
but the efficiency and cheap wiring of a "high voltage" system.</p></li></u=
l><hr data-path-to-node=3D"14"><h2 data-path-to-node=3D"15">4. Safety and S=
tandards (A Small "Peer" Warning)</h2><p data-path-to-node=3D"16">While 600=
V is great for efficiency, it is <b data-path-to-node=3D"16" data-index-in-=
node=3D"42">deadly</b>.</p><ul data-path-to-node=3D"17"><li><p data-path-to=
-node=3D"17,0,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"17,0,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">D=
C Arcs:</b> Unlike AC, DC current doesn't "pulse," so if an arc starts, it =
doesn't put itself out. It acts like a plasma torch.</p></li><li><p data-pa=
th-to-node=3D"17,1,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"17,1,0" data-index-in-node=3D=
"0">Rapid Shutdown:</b> Most modern 600V systems require "Rapid Shutdown" d=
evices (often built into optimizers) so that if the fire department cuts yo=
ur power, the roof voltage drops to a safe level (under 30V) instantly.</p>=
</li></ul><hr data-path-to-node=3D"18"><h3 data-path-to-node=3D"19">Compari=
son: 48V Parallel vs. 600V Optimized String</h3><div class=3D"horizontal-sc=
