th-to-node=3D"18">4. The "Frequency Shifting" Trick</h2><p data-path-to-nod=
e=3D"19">You might wonder: <i data-path-to-node=3D"19" data-index-in-node=
=3D"18">How does the Hybrid Inverter tell the Microinverters to stop produc=
ing power if the battery is 100% full during a blackout?</i></p><p data-pat=
h-to-node=3D"20">It uses a clever trick called <b data-path-to-node=3D"20" =
data-index-in-node=3D"30">Frequency Shifting</b>.</p><ul data-path-to-node=
=3D"21"><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"21,0,0">Standard AC is <b data-path-to-=
node=3D"21,0,0" data-index-in-node=3D"15">50Hz</b> or <b data-path-to-node=
=3D"21,0,0" data-index-in-node=3D"23">60Hz</b>.</p></li><li><p data-path-to=
-node=3D"21,1,0">If the battery is full, the Hybrid Inverter slightly incre=
ases the frequency (e.g., to <b data-path-to-node=3D"21,1,0" data-index-in-=
node=3D"87">61Hz</b> or <b data-path-to-node=3D"21,1,0" data-index-in-node=
=3D"95">62Hz</b>).</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"21,2,0">The Microinv=
erters are programmed to throttle down or shut off when they detect this hi=
gher frequency. This prevents the battery from overcharging.</p></li></ul><=
hr data-path-to-node=3D"22"><h3 data-path-to-node=3D"23">Which one should y=
ou choose?</h3><ul data-path-to-node=3D"24"><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"24,=
0,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"24,0,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">Choose Microi=
nverters (AC-Coupled)</b> if you have a complex roof with many angles, heav=
y shading, or if you want to start small and add panels one by one over sev=
eral years.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"24,1,0"><b data-path-to-nod=
e=3D"24,1,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">Choose a High-Voltage Hybrid (DC-Coup=
led)</b> if you have a clear, simple roof and your primary goal is the abso=
lute highest efficiency for charging your batteries.</p></li></ul><p data-p=
ath-to-node=3D"25"><b data-path-to-node=3D"25" data-index-in-node=3D"0">Wou=
ld you like me to find a diagram of a "Frequency Shift" power curve to show=
 exactly how the battery protects itself in an AC-coupled system?</b></p></=
