--animation-duration: 400ms; --fade-animation-function: linear;"><p data-pa=
th-to-node=3D"0">Here is the technical breakdown for building a 600W solar =
micro-inverter based on the <b data-path-to-node=3D"0" data-index-in-node=
=3D"86">Texas Instruments TIDA-010954</b> reference design.</p><p data-path=
-to-node=3D"1">This specific design, released in <b data-path-to-node=3D"1"=
 data-index-in-node=3D"34">April 2025</b>, is a masterpiece of modern power=
 electronics. It moves away from bulky, traditional silicon components and =
uses <b data-path-to-node=3D"1" data-index-in-node=3D"158">Gallium Nitride =
(GaN)</b> to achieve a power density that allows the entire 600W unit to fi=
t in a footprint smaller than a tablet (290mm x 100mm), all without a mecha=
nical heatsink.</p><h3 data-path-to-node=3D"2">1. <span class=3D"citation-1=
