-></response-element><hr data-path-to-node=3D"9"><h3 data-path-to-node=3D"1=
0">3. The "GaN Layout" Warning</h3><p data-path-to-node=3D"11">When you mov=
e from breadboarding with an Arduino to building a GaN-based microinverter =
with a C2000, your <b data-path-to-node=3D"11" data-index-in-node=3D"106">P=
CB Layout</b> becomes a component itself.</p><ul data-path-to-node=3D"12"><=
li><p data-path-to-node=3D"12,0,0"><b data-path-to-node=3D"12,0,0" data-ind=
ex-in-node=3D"0">Parasitic Inductance:</b> At 100kHz+, even a few millimete=
rs of extra trace length can cause "ringing" (voltage spikes) that will ins=
tantly destroy a GaN chip.</p></li><li><p data-path-to-node=3D"12,1,0"><b d=
ata-path-to-node=3D"12,1,0" data-index-in-node=3D"0">The Solution:</b> Use =
the <b data-path-to-node=3D"12,1,0" data-index-in-node=3D"22">Gerber files<=
/b> provided in the TI Design Guide. Do not try to manually route the high-=
speed power loops unless you have experience with high-frequency RF or Powe=
r PCB design.</p></li></ul><h3 data-path-to-node=3D"13">Next Step for You</=
h3><p data-path-to-node=3D"14">To get your hands on the actual code and har=
dware layouts, I recommend downloading the <b data-path-to-node=3D"14" data=
-index-in-node=3D"87">C2000Ware</b> software package from TI. It contains t=
he "DigitalPower SDK," which has the exact project folder for the 600W Micr=
oinverter.</p><p data-path-to-node=3D"15"><b data-path-to-node=3D"15" data-=
index-in-node=3D"0">Would you like me to find the link to the C2000Ware dow=
nload page or look up the specific "Evaluation Board" for the LMG2100 so yo=
u don't have to solder the tiny chips yourself for the first test?</b></p><=
